of 36 , 48 & of 5s8, provided there bee 20 demie peeces in one pack

soone as 20 p. of leverall sorts are ready, I have in ordered m. kent to
buij for mee the same quantitie that sordered you & that on the some day
shave all ready invoyces from him of half the quantitie, whilst I long
to know what passes & rest, insteed of 12 dosens 3:6 make 20 the same
about the 4s & 58 clothes ½ grajes & ½ mode cullours & all toilletted
af these are in w. 3:4 1 rest

S. mykast: to you was on y. 30 past, sence rec. yo of 18 p. gerge dhotson is well arrd
and S. convoy for hull by this time sailed from Dessel, there beinge & men of wans: you
have creditt for S bayles n°10 & n°11, and I exspect y rest of my orders compleat by y
first convoy for holland, & of this comes in time, so lett y dozens resting to my memoran=
dum, bee made up to 24 p for one pack for hull, either of y. low prices of 3:6
of 41: or 5ƒ, so as best shall bee roady to make a full bayle. I wish wee might have &
first convoij arriv from hull before y. netter of July, that so I might have time for annes
orders for ointere, intrim one will so ansos of hull is recomanded to mee because in henvy
met calf hath lest ofs trade, & hee hats order to ship some lead which I would not
have aboard such vessels, as shall have my packes therefore desireings you to write yo
frerid att hull, so lett him know in what ships hee shall London or hath Loneden n°
19 n°.S1, & p rest, that so 3 bee not to much intressed mone bottom, pray who is now
commessioner att Hull, that so I may omploye shim, wh Iiudge better, when hee knowes
what packes are for mee shippes accordinghey, I can day no more, then what allread f
have said abent f. sp clothes, 10 pray lett bee observed, & no opportunitie &ost for
them, foir white flannells, Bayes, and though one pack of white Cottons for holland
p. way of holland (for all I know, shall bee y. best, if y. frencss continue to bee masses
inflandre, so loose not anney opporounitie for holhand, if presents before that of
Oastend, for 0 place & ordered by 8 memorandum, to send 16 demye oed clothes
Inowdesire bee made up to 20, that is 4 single P. more p. ordered in P. menorandun
a 10 op these about, take no darck reds, butt auvesie cutt., und in case p. pack of

in antwort aenden ul van 27 pasato, ick hebbe tot londen soodanige ordre
gegeven dat int toecomende mijn haestige packen boven ingelaeden sullen sijn
de cognossementen op ostenden luyden en de schippers gewaersehout daer te lossen
waer van ul tijdelijck de cognossementen en kennisse sal geven, voor de reeckemis
de van oncosten hebbe ul provisionelijck gecrediteert hebbende geen tijdt gehadt
die naer te sien, gisteren sijn ons resterende packen hier eerst gelost, ingsloten
remitteere ul ƒ436:- court gelt ten latte mons. Andries de buck
in sijn brief van 6 xber lest 6 usos, gelieft de waerde in te voorderen
en ontfangen hebbende mijn avance mij te remitteere alsoo ick niet en twij
ffele oft ul heeft hier differente tot ul dispositie, versoecke advis vanden
ontfanck deses als mede te weten oft eenich convoij van ostende naer engelant
sal gaen dan ofte wij op engels convoij ons alleen moeten verlaeten het gene
voort eerst niet apparcht sal te verwachten sijn, nietse de scheepen
allen naer de groote vloot gaen blijvende naer groetenisse
